UID:89953-1780830000-1780835400@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Where Our Food Comes From
DESCRIPTION:Would you believe that watermelons used to be tiny and bitter? Can you imagine a carrot in any other colour? \nIn this interactive storytelling adventure\, children will travel across time and space to uncover the origins of ten fruits and vegetables — through vibrant visuals\, simple maps\, and sensory games. \nThere is a surprising history behind the food on your plate. Are you ready to discover it? \nParents\, please note: This is an interactive session tailored specifically to keep young minds engaged without heavy text—perfect for early learners! \nThis event is a part of the Environment Day programming at BIC. \nAround the World in 50 Sundays is a journey that begins\, not with a ticket\, but with opening a book. In a city like Bangalore where families are always in motion\, the BIC Library hopes to offer stillness and a quiet\, welcoming space for both parents and children where reading becomes a shared experience. \nEvery Sunday\, we open our doors to invite you into a library that listens; building a rhythm of return\, a habit of joy and a new community bound not just by books\, but by the weekly ritual of reading together. \nWe welcome your ideas and input. If you have suggestions for children’s events or activities that align with this vision\, we’d love to hear from you. Please reach out to us at library@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/where-our-food-comes-from/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Around the World in 50 Sundays
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thumbnail_WOFCF.jpg
END:VEVENT
