UID:90149-1781289000-1781294400@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:The Conscience of the Constitution
DESCRIPTION:Dignity has never arrived on its own.  \nIt has been argued for\, marched for\, litigated over\, and claimed inch by inch by movements that refused to wait. \nThis conversation brings together Justice S Muralidhar\, Siddharth Narrain\, and Ruth Manorama\, stalwarts in the fields of law\, gender and sexuality\, constitutionalism\, and anti-caste movements. Together they discuss what constitutional morality actually means in practice today\, where LGBTQIA+ and anti-caste movements have converged and diverged\, and what the law can and cannot do for people it has historically failed. \nWhat does a future of dignity\, respect and joy look life for queer India? \nIn Collaboration with: \n \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/the-conscience-of-the-constitution/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Gender,Law
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail_COC.jpg
END:VEVENT
